title: Sunshine and temperatures in the 70s expected this weekend
title_page: Sunshine and temperatures in the 70s expected this weekend
maintext:
Sunshine and temperatures in the 70s expected this weekend
Thereâ€™s a 10% chance of showers in Milwaukee before 7 a.m., Saturday, followed by two days of sunshine and temperatures in the 70s, according to the National Weather Service in Sullivan.
A high temperature near 75 degrees is expected Saturday, with mostly sunny skies and a northeast wind between 5-10 mph, according to the weather service.
Sunday is, again, expected to be sunny, with a high temperature near 77 degrees and, again, a northeast wind between 5-10 mph, according to the weather service forecast.
The high temperature in Milwaukee Friday was 76, 4 degrees lower than normal for July 29, according to the weather service.
